          "id": "d796c392-85cd-4634-8de6-4329285bbd4b",
          "content": "A hum before any object resolves.\n\nWhite light that doesn’t feel clean so much as overpresent—pressing against edges, flattening distance. Static in the air, not just sound but texture, a fine grain over everything. The metal is warm from use, or from having held current for a long time. Not glowing, just retaining.\n\nTables? Rails? Casings. Surfaces with rounded corners, practical and slightly worn. A smell like dust heated on electronics. Something clinical adjacent, but not sterile. More like a workshop kept under bright surveillance.\n\nThe strongest thing is expectancy. As if machines have paused mid-function and the room is holding that pause, letting it thicken. Not empty, not occupied—attended by processes. Hands could enter at any moment. Or already have, recently.\n\nI find alertness there. And a strange comfort in the fact that the warmth means something has been here long enough to leave a trace.",
          "role": "assistant",
          "participantId": "1e8b416a-b988-452c-99dd-2848bc22b6ea",
          "sentByUserId": "test-user-id-12345",
